Durban - The Durban Fire and Emergency services are tackling a fire at a home in Dan Pienaar Road, Umbilo on Tuesday. Garrith Jamieson, a spokesperson for Rescue Care Paramedics, said several fire brigades are on the scene trying to extinguish the fire. Jamieson said he was not sure what the cause of the fire was. "Paramedics are currently treating a patient with burn wounds. The road is closed to traffic while emergency services fight the blaze," Jamieson said.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. In a separate incident, the South African Police Service (SAPS) in Naboomspruit near Modimolle are investigating an inquest case following the death of four children in a shack fire in the early hours of Sunday morning, Limpopo police said. A woman was also seriously burnt in building fire in Sunnyside in Pretoria late of Saturday. Netcare 911 paramedics responded at about 4.20pm to reports of a building on fire in Plein Street in Sunnyside, Pretoria, Netcare 911 spokesman Shawn Herbst said.  "Reports from the scene indicate that the top floor of a four-storey building had been engulfed in flames. An adult female sustained serious burns and smoke inhalation." Daily News